name: .AXE File Extension
summary: Learn about .AXE files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: Locations file created by Microsoft AutoRoute, a map navigation and trip planning program for Eastern and Western Europe; contains "pushpins," which are Points of Interest (POI) on the map; can also contain navigation data.

content: AXE files are used for saving map locations and creating navigation routes in Europe. The files can be converted to many different POI data formats using POIConverter.
